Probabilistic Methods, Theory

Probabilistic Methods: The method described in the paper for change detection is based on the generation of T cells in the immune system, which involves probabilistic processes such as random recombination and mutation. The paper also discusses the use of probability distributions to model the behavior of computer viruses.

Theory: The paper presents a theoretical framework for understanding the problem of protecting computer systems as a problem of self-nonself discrimination. It also includes mathematical analysis of the computational costs of the proposed method.
